Note:
	Internal: /dev/disk3s3 â†’ â€œMacintosh HDâ€
	External: /dev/disk5s1 â†’ â€œExtMacOSâ€

3. sudo asr restore --source /dev/disk3s3 --target /dev/disk5s1 --erase --noprompt

4. Open Disk Utility and rename external Macintosh HD to ExtMacOS

ðŸŽ 4. For Apple Silicon (M1, M2, M3) Macs

Due to Sealed System Volume (SSV), a block-level clone may not boot.
Instead:

Boot into macOS Recovery (Power button â†’ hold â†’ Options â†’ Continue).

Erase internal or external drive as APFS.

Use Time Machine Restore or Migration Assistant to move data from the clone.

To clone Apple Silicon system volumes properly, you can use:

sudo asr restore --source / --target /Volumes/MacClone --erase --puppetstrings










Install OhMyZsh theme
sh -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh/master/tools/install.sh)"

Disable memory-hungry UI services (reversible)
defaults write com.apple.finder DisableAllAnimations -bool true
defaults write NSGlobalDomain NSAutomaticWindowAnimationsEnabled -bool false
killall Finder

Stop photo analysis (huge background RAM)
launchctl unload -w /System/Library/LaunchAgents/com.apple.photoanalysisd.plist
sudo launchctl bootout system /System/Library/LaunchDaemons/com.apple.photoanalysisd.plist

Mirror source to destination (exact copy)
rsync -av --delete source/ destination/
(Be careful: --delete removes files in the destination that do not exist in source.)




